This table is based on documents (where doc_id is unique) uploaded through Turbo Tax Live through four upload mechanisms:

title: Device Type Name

title: CR Numerator
description: Contact Resolution numerator from the post contact survey sent after a customer has connected with a care agent. Used to calculate the contact resolution rate. Positive answer indicates that the customer feels that we have answered their question.

title: CR Denominator
description: Contact Resolution denominator from the post contact survey sent after a customer has connected with a care agent. Used to calculate the contact resolution rate. Indicates whether the customer responded to this. question in the survey.

title: Assisted Pro Usage Indicator

title: App Type Name
description: The application type associated with the first session for the test. Classifed as 'Stationary Web','Mobile App', and 'Mobile Web' and is derived from the dim_user_agent_id table.

title: Any Tile Selection Flag

title: TurboTax Self Employed Assisted Users
description: Flags auth_ids that submitted a contact request through self help. Does not include direct dial (i.e. dialed from Google search) calls.

title: TurboTax Self Employed Assisted Count
description: Count of Assisted Contact Submissions through the web. This is a total count, so can be > 1 if a customer submitted more than one request. Used to calculated Assisted Contact Rate.

title: TurboTax Online Segment Rupee
description: The rollup of 'New' and 'Skip Year' to 'New' and '1st Year Returning' and 'Veteran Returning' to 'Returning'. The marketing acquisition/retention segment of a TTO auth_id, derived only from AUTH_ID-based information. 'New', 'Skip Year', '1st Year Returning', 'Veteran Returning,' generally indicating the last time the auth_id last completed tax prep with Turbo Tax Online. 'Returning' means the auth_Id completed tax prep in the prior year and 'New' means they did not (though doesn't necessarily mean the auth_id was actually created in the current tax year).

title: TurboTax Online Segment
description: The marketing acquisition/retention segment of a TTO auth_id, derived only from AUTH_ID-based information. 'New', 'Skip Year', '1st Year Returning', 'Veteran Returning,' generally indicating the last time the auth_id last completed tax prep with Turbo Tax Online.

title: Point of Need Down Votes

title: Net Promoter Promoters

title: Net Promoter Passives
description: Transactional Net Promotor Score passive response from the post contact survey sent after a customer has connected with a care agent. Used to calculate tNPS. Indicates that a customer gave a 7 or 8 score.

title: Net Promoter Detractors
description: Transactional Net Promotor Score detractor from the post contact survey sent after a customer has connected with a care agent. Used to calculate tNPS. Indicates that a customer gave a 0-6 score.

After TY18: it is based on the tax complexity, not the actual tax form the users use

title: CR Numerator
description: Contact Resolution numerator from the post contact survey sent after a customer has connected with a care agent. Used to calculate the contact resolution rate. Positive answer indicates that the customer feels that we have answered their question.

title: CR Denominator
description: Contact Resolution denominator from the post contact survey sent after a customer has connected with a care agent. Used to calculate the contact resolution rate. Indicates whether the customer responded to this question in the survey.

title: Completed SKU
description: The product SKU a user purchased in TTO (completed = paid for Credit Card user and E-file attempted for Refund Transfer users).

title: Completed Flag
description: A binary (1 = completed, 0 = not completed) field that suggests if the user has paid for TTO/TTU. Credit Card users complete at payment and Refund Transfer users complete at their first E-file attempt.

title: Care Entitlement Level
description: What level of entitelment does a customer have to care access

title: Auth ID Range Role
description: Described whether the AuthID is "new" or "existing" for this tax season based on if the AuthID existed prior to the first day of this tax season.

title: Assisted Pro Usage
description: Auth Id used a tax pro, meaning that they connected with a tax pro on the phone. A pro is exclusive to Tax Advice, and typically only for TurboTax Live. Does not include other call types like Product Support, Tax Support, etc.

title: Last Tabl Name
description: Name of the last tab seen by user

title: Last Screen
description: Last screen seen by user

title: entry page group
description: the landing page the user landed on from external pages

title: order amount
description: the total amount paid for filing taxes

title: start sku
description: the sku a user start his taxes with

title: channel
description: marketing (advertisement) channel

title: customer type rollup
description: customer segments rolled up (new, existing)

title: Nonffa Flag
description: A 1 or 0 flag indicating that a user could be a part of the Free Filing Alliance population that is referred to Turbo Tax Online from the IRS FFA Portal. FFA usres are generally not considered part of the commercial opportunity for TTO.

title: PRS Score
description: Stands for "Product Recommendation Score", a scale of 1-10, presented to user directly after e-file. This field takes a varying percentage of samples each year. PRS is a specific definition of the more widely known Net Promoter Score or NPS, but with the question more specifically towards the recommendation of the TTO Product rather than a recommendation of a Brand.

title: PRS timestamp
description: Product recommendation score timestamp

title: Completed TTL Proxy SKU
description: Product SKU name of the TTL product used to complete the tax filing

title: Core Flag
description: A flag that is currently primarily used to indicate the "core business opportunity" population of users. Right now, the core_flag is just the opposite of the existence of a multifiler_timestamp. A user identified as a multi-filer is non-core. A non-multifiler user is considered Core. This core_flag contained multiple definitions in the past to "provide uniformity" on the true business opportunity.

title: First Start Date
description: The first date within a Tax Year a user "started" Tax Prep. UX-wise Tax Prep is defined as having pushed the "Start My Taxes" button or was automatically pass through to "Tax Prep". Previous definitions used the actual TTO "Session Start" logs to indicate Start, once GTKM was added this changed to the current definition of "Any users with a TTO Session Start Log or a GTKM Beacon (since GTKM doesn't have server session logs).

title: Tto Segment Rollup
description: The rollup of 'New' and 'Skip Year' to 'New' and '1st Year Returning' and 'Veteran Returning' to 'Returning'. The marketing acquisition/retention segment of a TTO auth_id, derived only from AUTH_ID-based information. 'New', 'Skip Year', '1st Year Returning', 'Veteran Returning,' generally indicating the last time the auth_id last completed tax prep with Turbo Tax Online. 'Returning' means the auth_Id completed tax prep in the prior year and 'New' means they did not (though doens't necessarily mean the auth_id was actually created in the current tax year).

title: First Federal Efile Rejected Date Adjusted
description: Adjusted date (reporting date to account for yoy day of week change) when a user's first e-file attempt of their federal return is rejected by IRS.

title: Multifiler Timestamp
description: The first date within a Tax Year a user is associated with a Multi-filer visitor. A Multi-filer visitor is a device/cookie based Visitor ID (Omnitures definition) that has more than 5 Auth ID's associated with it. The timestamp is the greater of the timestamp associated with 6th association of an AUTH_ID to VISITOR_ID or the timestamp associated between the auth_Id and visitor.

title: Start Sku Rollup
description: A rollup of the Start SKU into Free and Paid SKUs. Thus this mainly rolls up the Paid SKUs together differentiating them the Free SKU.

title: Start Experience
description: A column that is used to describe the various "start" experiences which have existed over the years. Currently most people get the Get To Know Me (GTKM) Start Experience, but there are still some device/browsers which are not supported and thus some users still have a "Classic" start experience where they go straight into Turbo Tax Online.

title: Num Schedule F
description: Number of Schedule F schedules attached to the tax return at time of filing. Schedule F has to do with income or loss as part of operating a Farm.

title: Sessions To Complete
description: Number of sessions a customer entered in to before completing tax prep.

title: First Federal Efile Accepted Date Adjusted
description: Adjusted date (reporting date to account for yoy day of week change) when a user's first e-file attempt of their federal return is accepted by IRS.

title: Tto Segment Hybrid
description: The marketing acquisition/retention segment of a TTO auth_id, derived from both AUTH_ID-based information and is updated for the next year using HASH-SSN information after a user completes. . 'New', 'Skip Year', '1st Year Returning', 'Veteran Returning,' generally indicating the last time the auth_id last completed tax prep with Turbo Tax Online.

title: First State Code Efiled
description: The 2 character code (CA for California) of a state for which the user first attempted to e-file, whether accepted or not. If a user attempts to file multiple states, this field will capture the first one they e-filed. This value will be null if the user does not file any states.

title: Pseudonym Identifier
description: Psuedonym id for the customer

title: First Vauth Date Adj
description: The first date within a Tax Year a user was VERIFIED to have completed authentication into TTO. A Verified authenication is different from the NEAuth in that the user in confirmed to have made it through any secondary/MFA type of challenges. "Adjusted" means it changes the date in prior Tax Years to match with the current year.

title: Vauth User Agent Identify
description: The user_agent_id associated with the first VAuth event for the given user and tax year. User Agent ID can be used to derive the Application Type, Device, Operating System, and Browser information.

title: Num Schedule B
description: Number of Schedule B schedules attached to the tax return at time of filing. Schedule B tends to reflect passive income gained from Interest or Dividends.

title: Start Platform Type
description: The platform type associated with the first Start event for the given user and tax year (usually a GTKM beacon). Platforms types are generally OS-device related like 'iOS','Android', 'Stationary OS', etc. Platform type is derived from the user_agent_id.

title: Neauth User Agent Identify
description: The user_agent_id associated with the first NEAuth event for the given user and tax year. User Agent ID can be used to derive the Application Type, Device, Operating System, and Browser information.

title: Neauth Device Type
description: The device type associated with the first NEAuth event for the given user and tax year. Device types are 'Stationary',Phone', 'Tablet', etc. Device type is derived from the user_agent_id.

title: Num Schedule A
description: Number of Schedule A schedules attached to the tax return at time of filing. There can only be 0 or 1 Schedule A's and the presence of Schedule A means a user was considered "Itemized."

title: Completed Flag
description: A binary (1 = completed, 0 = not completed) field that suggests if the user has paid for TTO/TTU. Credit Card users complete at payment, Free-Pay Nothing ($0) Users at "Registration", and Refund Transfer users complete at their first E-file attempt.

title: Neauth App Type
description: The application type associated with the first NEAuth event for the given user and tax year. Application types are 'Stationary Web','Mobile App', and 'Mobile Web'. App type is derived from the user_agent_id.

title: Vauth Flag
description: A 1 or 0 flag indicating that a vauth_timestamp exists. VAuth is a "Verified" auth_id who has successful authorized beyond any secondary MFA challenges if they were presented.

title: Tto Start Flag
description: A 1 or 0 flag indicating the a first_start_date exists. That a user "started tax prep" for the given tax_year by reaching Get To Know Me or generated a start session log from TTO.

title: Start TTL Proxy SKU
description: TTL Proxy SKU for customer when customer start filing

title: Form Filings Are Date Adj
description:
The date/timestamp that a user is first associated with being a User direct to Turbo Tax Online from the IRS Free File Alliance portal. FFA Users are generally not considered a commercial opportunity. The date is derived from a user completing in an FFA SKU or Started in a FFA SKU.


"Adjusted" means the date is adjusted to the same day of the week in the current year. (Via multiples of 364 days).

title: First Multifiler Date Adj
description:
The first date within a Tax Year a user is associated with a Multi-filer visitor. A Multi-filer visitor is a device/cookie based Visitor ID (Omnitures definition) that has more than 5 Auth ID's associated with it. The timestamp is the greater of the timestamp associated with 6th association of an AUTH_ID to VISITOR_ID or the timestamp associated between the auth_Id and visitor.


"Adjusted" means it changes the date in prior Tax Years to match with the current year.

title: First Start Date Adj
description:
The first date within a Tax Year a user "started" Tax Prep. UX-wise Tax Prep is defined as having pushed the "Start My Taxes" button or was automatically pass through to "Tax Prep". Previous definitions used the actual TTO "Session Start" logs to indicate Start, once GTKM was added this changed to the current definition of "Any users with a TTO Session Start Log or a GTKM Beacon (since GTKM doesn't have server session logs).

"Adjusted" means it changes the date in prior Tax Years to match with the current year.

title: Num Searched

title: Pay Customer Type

IS this user considered a 'new' or 'existing customer? py_ means that this is the definition of the customer_type in the prior year and is only available for users who completed in the prior year to trigger the flow of the HASHED-SSN Identity.

title: Pay Customer Type Rollup

A rollup of py_customer_type to 'New' and 'Existing'.


Customer Type generally means that a HASHED-SSN identity is being used to determine a customer Marketing Acquisition/Retention metrics and insights. title: Pay Fed Form Type

The Fed Form Type which prior to Tax Year 2018 indicated some level of Tax Complexity. This field is derived from the TaxML Data and if not null indicates the 1040 Long 'F1040', 1040A 'F1040A', or 1040EZ 'F1040EZ'.


"py" indicates this was the fed form type from the previous/prior tax year.

title: Voicemail Flag

Indicates if an agent indicates reaching voicemail; this is NOT a vetted field


                max(case when end_type='CALLBACK ATTEMPT' then 1 else 0 end) as voicemail_flg,

title: Transferred To Queue
description:
Queue of next call within one customer call flow


        lead(offered_queue) over(partition by cc_id order by offer_seq) as transferred_to_queue,

title: Transferred From Queue
description:
Queue of preceding call within one customer call flow


        lag(offered_queue) over(partition by cc_id order by offer_seq) as transferred_from_queue

title: Transferred Flag

title: Request Timestamp
description:
for transfers, offered start timestamp; for non transfers it's the lowest value of : enrich_date, createddate (both from salesforce), or offered start date from amazon connect.  


case when lag(transferred_flg) over(partition by cc_id order by offer_seq)=1 then offered_start_ts
                else least(coalesce(enrich_date__c,createddate),offered_start_ts) end as request_ts,

title: Queued Flag
description: Indicates if a call sat in a queue

title: Offered Type
description: Call type per call. If there is a callback that is transferred as an inbound- sourced from amazon connect, changes with amazon connect changes, primarily used to determine callback vs inbound.

title: Offered Start Timestamp
description: First start timestamp for the call; this could be leg_type='AGENT' or 'QUEUE'

title: Offered Flag
description: Always 1, because this table is at the offered contact level.  an offered contact is any attempt by a customer to connect with an expert in customer success

title: Offered First Queue
description: Same as offered_queue

title: Offered End Timestamp
description: Last end timestamp for the call; this could be leg_type='AGENT' or 'QUEUE'

title: Last Agent Source Key
description:
Last source_key from care_dwh.fact_cc_source_mapping where leg_type='AGENT'- this is the last agent that talked to a customer in a contact flow.  This logic mirrors our saleforce logic where the last agent on a call gets credit for the survery of that call. 


last_value(case when leg_type='AGENT' then source_key end ignore nulls) over(partition by cc_id,offer_seq order by cc_leg_num rows between unbounded preceding and unbounded following) as last_agent_source_key


care_dwh.fact_cc_source_mapping

title: Is Transfer Flag
description:
Indicates if a call is a result of a transfer


max(case when leg_type='AGENT' and adj_handled_flg=1 and agent_id=leg_agent
                        and end_type in ('TRANSFER TO AGENT','TRANSFER TO QUEUE','TRANSFER TO EXTERNAL NUMBER') then 1 else 0 end) as transferred_flg,

title: Interaction Skill Language

title: Interaction Skill Country
description: region_iso_code from qbskillmap_skill_groupings.  Country associated with the routed queue; unrelated to the agent country served field, as this solely depends on the queue itself

title: Initiated Type
description: Call type per call flow. If there is a callback that is transferred as an inbound.  This differs from offered_type as offered_types uses the first call type from the first interaction of a call flow.

title: Inet Key
description:
iNET key- for inet/IVR calls only, so we can link this call to the inet experience. the id itself comes from care_dwh.fact_cc_source_mapping


                first_value(case when m.src_system='INET' then m.source_key end ignore nulls) over(partition by c.cc_id order by c.cc_leg_num) as inet_key,

title: Hold Seconds
description: Seconds in hold state where leg_type='AGENT'

title: Handled Flag
description:
handled count here differs from amazon connect's handle logic.  If a call is outbound and talk duration is greater than 60 seconds, then handled. 

for all other call types, if talk duration is greater than 60 seconds, the handled.



max(case when agent_id=leg_agent then adj_handled_flg else 0 end) as handled_flg,

case when leg_queue like '%outbound%' then case when talk_dur>60 then 1 else 0 end
                        when c.callback_type<>'N/A' then case when talk_dur>60 then 1 else 0 end
                        when talk_dur>0 then 1
                        else 0 end as adj_handled_flg
Indicates if the call/record has been "handled"

title: Forecast Group Name

title: Exceeded Appointment Time Seconds

Seconds beyond a scheduled appointment time that the call was initiated


sum(nvl(case when callback_type='CALLBACK SCHEDULED' then exceeded_promised_callback_dur end,0)) as exceeded_appt_time_seconds,
